# Local OpenFX onboarding environment (gitignored — DO NOT COMMIT).
#
# This is a PLAIN KEY=value data file. The skill PARSES it — it does NOT `source`/execute it — so
# values are read literally and no shell is ever run from this file or from your downloaded
# credential files. Load everything via the skill's helper (the one trusted, shipped script):
#
#     source "<this skill's dir>/scripts/dotenv.sh"
#     load_openfx_env sandbox          # or: load_openfx_env prod
#
# load_openfx_env exports TESSER_*/OPENFX_* by:
#   - reading the optional overrides below (allowlisted keys only),
#   - deriving Tesser creds from ./tesser-credentials*.env   (CLIENT_ID / CLIENT_SECRET),
#   - deriving OpenFX values  from ./OpenFX_api-key_*.json   (orgId / id / privateKey, via jq),
#   - pinning the Tesser API + Auth0 hosts to a fixed allowlist.
# The ES256 private key is NEVER stored here — it's read from the JSON each time you load.

# --- The one value you add by hand (after creating the OpenFX webhook — SKILL.md Phase 1b) ---
# Set it with the helper, which upserts it without echoing:  set_openfx_webhook_secret '<signing key>'
# OPENFX_WEBHOOK_SECRET=

# --- Optional endpoint overrides (must stay on the Tesser/Auth0 allowlist, or loading aborts) ---
# Prefer `load_openfx_env prod` over overriding by hand; these exist only for staging variants.
# TESSER_BASE_URL=https://api.tesser.xyz
# TESSER_AUDIENCE=https://api.tesser.xyz
# TESSER_AUTH_URL=https://tesser-payments.us.auth0.com/oauth/token
